Chartwell adopts shareholder right plan . Chartwell Re Corp said Thursday its board adopted a shareholder rights plan . The company said the plan calls for it to distribute a dividend of one preferred share purchase right for each outstanding share of its common stock . It said the rights would be exercisable only if a person or group acquires 20 percent or more of its common stock or announces a tender offer that would lead to 20 percent ownership . The record date for the rights distribution is May 22 and the rights will expire ten years later unless they are redeemed earlier by the company . The rights distribution is not taxable to stockholders . Chartwell Re ' s wholly - owned subsidiaries writes property , casualty , marine and aviation reinsurance . 
